1
00:01:06,239 --> 00:01:08,000
Do you know about CS, the hottest game right now?

2
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,079
The one where you take an AK and go rat-a-tat-tat?

3
00:01:10,079 --> 00:01:10,519
You know?

4
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,280
Young people love playing this the most right now.

5
00:01:12,599 --> 00:01:13,959
They stay up all night playing it.

6
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:15,599
CS.

7
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:17,560
This game is indeed fast approaching...

8
00:01:17,560 --> 00:01:18,959
...the moment it explodes in popularity.

9
00:01:20,879 --> 00:01:22,280
So what can I do...

10
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:24,159
...to utilize that plot of land at the playground?

11
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:26,280
You just reminded me.

12
00:01:27,599 --> 00:01:28,640
What's the fun in playing virtually?

13
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:30,239
If we're gonna play, let's play for real.

14
00:01:30,519 --> 00:01:31,760
We'll use that playground lot...

15
00:01:31,799 --> 00:01:33,920
...and start a Live-Action Shooting Club.

16
00:01:34,760 --> 00:01:35,560
What do you think?

17
00:01:35,719 --> 00:01:36,799
Darn it, Brother Fan.

18
00:01:36,799 --> 00:01:38,680
Your brain really works fast.

19
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:39,920
Hey, Brother Liang.

20
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:41,280
Do you want to join us?

21
00:01:41,599 --> 00:01:42,599
The two of us definitely can't handle it alone.

22
00:01:42,959 --> 00:01:44,840
I support you guys 100% in spirit.

23
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:45,920
But lately...

24
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:47,120
...I really have too much on my plate.

25
00:01:47,319 --> 00:01:48,159
Actually...

26
00:01:48,439 --> 00:01:50,640
...I've been tinkering with antivirus software recently.

27
00:01:50,879 --> 00:01:52,120
I wanted to talk to you about it...

28
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,560
...and test the waters at the internet cafe.

29
00:01:53,719 --> 00:01:54,799
But looking at it now...

30
00:01:54,799 --> 00:01:56,239
...I'm afraid you won't have time to work on it with me.

31
00:01:56,319 --> 00:01:57,400
Who says I don't have time?

32
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,519
We have to do the Live-Action CS...

33
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,359
...but we also have to get your antivirus software going.

34
00:02:02,079 --> 00:02:04,799
But the profit from software isn't as high as games.

35
00:02:05,319 --> 00:02:06,359
Why do you want to do this?

36
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,199
Chen Fan.

37
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:10,400
There's something...

38
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:12,759
...I want to confess to you.

39
00:02:13,159 --> 00:02:14,120
What is it?

40
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,280
As long as it's not a love confession...

41
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,080
...anything else is fine.

42
00:02:19,479 --> 00:02:21,520
During the college entrance exams last summer...

43
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:23,240
...your website was attacked by a hacker.

44
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:24,840
Do you remember that?

45
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:26,599
How do you kn...

46
00:02:28,919 --> 00:02:29,479
Don't tell me...

47
00:02:29,479 --> 00:02:30,479
I did it.

48
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,159
Darn it.

49
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,639
I was young back then...

50
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,719
...and wanted to make some quick money.

51
00:02:35,039 --> 00:02:36,599
I took an anonymous job online...

52
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:38,479
...and attacked your website's server.

53
00:02:38,759 --> 00:02:40,240
So we crossed paths a long time ago.

54
00:02:40,439 --> 00:02:42,199
When you traced my IP address back then...

55
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:43,439
...I was worried you'd retaliate.

56
00:02:44,599 --> 00:02:46,199
But I waited a long time and heard nothing.

57
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:47,840
So I went back on DomainNet to take a look.

58
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,199
And I found out...

59
00:02:49,759 --> 00:02:51,560
...you not only analyzed the incident...

60
00:02:52,439 --> 00:02:54,599
...but also made a tutorial and shared it for free.

61
00:02:55,039 --> 00:02:56,479
That was the first time I realized...

62
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:59,080
...cybersecurity isn't a means to show off skills...

63
00:02:59,599 --> 00:03:01,159
...but to protect everyone's hard work.

64
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,199
So...

65
00:03:04,639 --> 00:03:05,960
...you decided to wash your hands of it?

66
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,199
I destroyed all my hacking tools...

67
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,719
...and spent a long time researching again.

68
00:03:12,199 --> 00:03:13,120
I just wanted to create a tool...

69
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,319
...that can protect ordinary internet users...

70
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:15,840
...and defend against malicious attacks.

71
00:03:16,199 --> 00:03:17,159
Later, I met you.

72
00:03:17,639 --> 00:03:18,960
After finding out we were roommates...

73
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,479
...I wanted to apologize to you several times.

74
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:22,599
But...

75
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,280
...I really didn't know how to bring it up.

76
00:03:26,319 --> 00:03:27,159
It's all in the past.

77
00:03:28,039 --> 00:03:29,400
A reformed man is worth his weight in gold.

78
00:03:30,039 --> 00:03:30,599
Besides...

79
00:03:30,599 --> 00:03:31,159
...actually...

80
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:33,280
...you didn't cause me any substantial loss.

81
00:03:33,599 --> 00:03:35,120
On the contrary, because of that attack and defense...

82
00:03:35,199 --> 00:03:36,240
...DomainNet's security...

83
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,599
...gained recognition from more users.

84
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:39,719
How about this.

85
00:03:39,919 --> 00:03:41,120
Once I'm free in a couple of days...

86
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:42,919
...let's have a good talk about the development direction.

87
00:03:43,199 --> 00:03:43,560
Really?

88
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:44,000
Yeah.

89
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,080
You're still willing to work with me?

90
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,360
Of course.

91
00:03:48,199 --> 00:03:49,199
It's all in the past, all in the past.

92
00:03:49,319 --> 00:03:49,560
Come on.

93
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:50,840
Brothers united...

94
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,360
...can cut through gold.

95
00:03:55,319 --> 00:03:55,759
Let's do this.

96
00:04:04,439 --> 00:04:05,000
Brother Fan

97
00:04:05,879 --> 00:04:06,840
If I get sentenced...

98
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,439
Take care of my parents for me.

99
00:04:08,439 --> 00:04:08,759
Guo Shuai

100
00:04:08,759 --> 00:04:09,240
Hey, stop!

101
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:09,639
Guo Shuai

102
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,080
Stop!

103
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:10,439
Brother Fan

104
00:04:10,439 --> 00:04:11,240
Officer, what's going on?

105
00:04:11,479 --> 00:04:12,199
Armed assault.

106
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,039
The victim is still being resuscitated in the ER.

107
00:04:14,159 --> 00:04:15,280
The nature of this incident is very serious.

108
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:19,399
Right.

109
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,639
In my past life, Guo Shuai accidentally stabbed someone.

110
00:04:21,639 --> 00:04:22,439
It was right around this time.

111
00:04:23,279 --> 00:04:24,160
I have to stop him.

112
00:04:26,879 --> 00:04:27,560
Brother Fan

113
00:04:27,959 --> 00:04:29,120
You have to bring Ruochu.

114
00:04:29,319 --> 00:04:31,319
To cheer for my Ling Ling at the dance competition.

115
00:04:31,639 --> 00:04:33,120
Otherwise, Ling Ling will be mad at me.

116
00:04:33,519 --> 00:04:34,399
Let me tell you.

117
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:35,639
My best friend from high school.

118
00:04:35,639 --> 00:04:36,360
But don't be nervous.

119
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:37,240
They're all really nice people.

120
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,800
And Chen Fan is really amazing.

121
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,319
You know?

122
00:04:39,839 --> 00:04:40,399
What are you chatting about?

123
00:04:40,399 --> 00:04:41,079
Hey, Brother Fan.

124
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,120
Long time no see.

125
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:45,959
Hi.

126
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,639
Cheers.

127
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,720
Let's wish Ling Ling all the best for tomorrow.

128
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:01,399
All the best.

129
00:05:01,519 --> 00:05:02,399
Thank you, everyone.

130
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:05,600
By the way.

131
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:07,199
Who's going to cheer for Ling Ling tomorrow?

132
00:05:07,879 --> 00:05:08,600
Just us.

133
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,199
Her classmates are all out competing.

134
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,360
Wait, why do you ask?

135
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:12,920
Idiot.

136
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,600
In the last life, because of the people cheering...

137
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,480
...and heckling around Ling Ling...

138
00:05:15,639 --> 00:05:16,959
...you got jealous and caused an incident.

139
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:19,040
I can't let you stumble again.

140
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:20,279
Brother Fan?

141
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,199
It's nothing.

142
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,240
I was just asking.

143
00:05:24,279 --> 00:05:24,759
Sister-in-law.

144
00:05:25,759 --> 00:05:26,680
Eat up.

145
00:05:28,439 --> 00:05:29,079
Thanks, thanks.

146
00:05:29,079 --> 00:05:29,600
You eat more too.

147
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,519
Ling Ling, you eat too.

148
00:05:33,279 --> 00:05:34,839
Tell me about you and Brother Fan.

149
00:05:34,839 --> 00:05:36,240
Back in high school, Brother Fan didn't listen in class.

150
00:05:36,399 --> 00:05:38,319
So he got punished by standing in the hallway.

151
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,439
Here, Sister Ruochu.

152
00:05:40,839 --> 00:05:41,720
All the best!

153
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,680
What else? Tell me more.

154
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,120
Brother Fan and I were real troublemakers in high school.

155
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,199
Come on, cheers.

156
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,879
Tomorrow will definitely go smoothly.

157
00:06:03,439 --> 00:06:04,879
I'm fine.

158
00:06:05,199 --> 00:06:06,120
Chen Fan.

159
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:09,199
Hurry up and pour me some wine.

160
00:06:13,959 --> 00:06:15,319
You drank so much even though you can't handle it.

161
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:16,839
I'll go pour you a glass of water.

162
00:06:17,199 --> 00:06:18,160
You're not allowed to leave.

163
00:06:19,199 --> 00:06:20,560
You can't skip out on drinking.

164
00:06:21,639 --> 00:06:22,439
Cheers.

165
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:30,879
So after this drink, is it time for bed?

166
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:31,560
Okay.

167
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:34,920
Ruochu.

168
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,360
I know you probably can't hear me right now.

169
00:06:37,959 --> 00:06:39,279
And even if you did, you wouldn't remember.

170
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,079
But I still want to tell you.

171
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:44,800
In my last life, I failed to protect you.

172
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,879
But since I'm back this time...

173
00:06:47,639 --> 00:06:49,040
I will definitely keep you safe.

174
00:06:50,279 --> 00:06:51,920
I won't let you get hurt ever again.

175
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:12,199
Hello?

176
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,000
Brother Fan.

177
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:13,800
Come help, quick!

178
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,120
Guo Shuai got into a fight!

179
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:16,720
What?

180
00:07:17,879 --> 00:07:18,680
Stop fighting!

181
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,160
Stop fighting!

182
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:23,199
Guo Shuai!

183
00:07:23,199 --> 00:07:23,519
Get up.

184
00:07:23,639 --> 00:07:24,000
Let's go!

185
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:25,319
Stop! Stop!

186
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:26,279
Don't run!

187
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:28,160
Stop!

188
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:35,839
We lost them.

189
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:38,879
How dare they harass Ling Ling!

190
00:07:39,279 --> 00:07:40,600
I'll kill them!

191
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,439
Brother Fan, enough.

192
00:07:45,399 --> 00:07:46,399
Where's my knife?

193
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,879
Do you know how many years you'll get for stabbing someone?

194
00:07:48,879 --> 00:07:49,680
Do you think it's worth it?

195
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,399
Yeah, Guo Shuai.

196
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:53,800
Brother Fan is right.

197
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:55,759
Why are you so stupid?

198
00:07:56,519 --> 00:07:57,120
But Ling Ling...

199
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,519
I can't watch them bully you!

200
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:02,879
You brat.

201
00:08:03,319 --> 00:08:04,240
If it weren't for Ling Ling...

202
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,000
You'd be screwed for life.

203
00:08:06,439 --> 00:08:06,959
Brother Fan.

204
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,680
Thanks for today.

205
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,160
I have to take her back now.

206
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,399
She has a competition tomorrow.

207
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,560
I'll get a taxi to take you home.

208
00:08:15,879 --> 00:08:16,560
No need, Brother Fan.

209
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,639
I can handle it myself.

210
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:22,199
Let's go.

211
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:24,040
Let's go.

212
00:08:25,399 --> 00:08:25,920
Keys.

213
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:27,600
Thanks, Brother Fan.

214
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,160
Let's go, come on.

215
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:37,320
Guo Shuai.

216
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:42,519
Guo Shuai!

217
00:08:44,679 --> 00:08:45,679
Guo Shuai, wake up!

218
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:46,799
Guo Shuai!

219
00:08:46,799 --> 00:08:47,279
Why?

220
00:08:47,559 --> 00:08:49,320
Why is this outcome still inevitable?

221
00:08:49,399 --> 00:08:50,000
Why?

222
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:50,919
Guo Shuai.

223
00:09:01,759 --> 00:09:02,279
Family of Guo Shuai?

224
00:09:02,279 --> 00:09:02,840
Doctor.

225
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,159
Doctor, how is he?

226
00:09:04,759 --> 00:09:06,279
The patient has a comminuted fracture of the right lower leg.

227
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,559
Severe nerve necrosis.

228
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:10,159
Whether we can save it depends on his recovery.

229
00:09:10,519 --> 00:09:11,720
You should comfort the patient.

230
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:12,639
At least he's still alive.

231
00:09:13,279 --> 00:09:14,960
There's always hope for the leg.

232
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:16,559
Doctor...

233
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,720
How did this happen?

234
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:22,919
It's all my fault.

235
00:09:22,919 --> 00:09:23,799
I failed to look after him.

236
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:29,919
Why, despite foreseeing everything...

237
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:31,799
...I still couldn't avoid it?

238
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,039
Don't lie to me.

239
00:09:34,039 --> 00:09:35,440
I know about my leg.

240
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:35,720
I'm scared that I...

241
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:36,440
Guo Shuai.

242
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:42,639
Take as much as you need.

243
00:09:47,759 --> 00:09:49,159
As long as I'm here, you won't be crippled.

244
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,840
Just rest here and recover.

245
00:09:50,879 --> 00:09:52,720
Surgery fees, hospitalization, rehab costs...

246
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,759
I'll cover it all.

247
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:54,879
If they can't cure you here...

248
00:09:54,879 --> 00:09:55,799
I'll take you abroad for treatment.

249
00:09:55,919 --> 00:09:57,200
We'll find the best doctors.

250
00:09:58,159 --> 00:09:59,480
Brother Fan.

251
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:01,720
Didn't you say...

252
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,519
...you'd go wherever Brother Fan goes?

253
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,000
I'll wait for you to get better.

254
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,480
To keep being my sidekick.

255
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:11,519
Alright.

256
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:12,720
Stop crying.

257
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:13,799
Lie down.

258
00:10:21,519 --> 00:10:23,600
Chen Fan, are you okay?

259
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:24,960
Are you hurt too?

260
00:10:25,879 --> 00:10:26,679
I'm fine.

261
00:10:29,159 --> 00:10:31,000
I was scared to death when I saw the message this morning.

262
00:10:31,559 --> 00:10:32,440
How is Guo Shuai?

263
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,080
What exactly happened?

264
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,519
It's a long story.

265
00:10:37,879 --> 00:10:39,399
Luckily I sent you back early.

266
00:10:39,679 --> 00:10:41,039
The situation was so urgent last night.

267
00:10:41,039 --> 00:10:42,480
Why didn't you tell me?

268
00:10:42,759 --> 00:10:44,519
Maybe with one more person, things would...

269
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:58,320
I will never let you

270
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,480
face such danger again.

271
00:11:03,759 --> 00:11:05,320
I promise to protect you.

272
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,720
I know you mean well.

273
00:11:10,759 --> 00:11:11,360
But...

274
00:11:11,759 --> 00:11:13,639
don't always talk about protecting me.

275
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,039
If something really happens,

276
00:11:15,879 --> 00:11:16,799
we'll face it together.
